<TITLE> China-Congo investment deal totals $9 bln-minister </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 KINSHASA, Feb 15 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A loan and investment accord signed by China with Congo will provide $9 billion for the African country's mining sector and infrastructure, much more than previously announced, the planning minister said on Friday. The overall value given by Planning Minister Olivier Kamitatu for the accord signed on Jan. 28 was much higher than the $5 billion price tag originally put on the deal when it was first announced last year in the Democratic Republic of Congo
